whenever it came my way; what you’ve taken is yours, there is no such thing as one’s own or another’s money; you don’t find written on a coin: belongs to Müller. I like money. I’ve always wished to find a faithful friend; we’d have made music together, he’d have bequeathed me his house and his orchard. Money, darling money. Darling small money. Darling big money. I roved about; found work here and there. One day I met a swell fellow who kept saying he was like me. Nonsense, he was